social_posts.post_text:
One thing I say every year is that I am going to get better at posting more frequently and inevitably fail. I’m not sure why this platform seems so overwhelming to me but it just is. I’m sure a lot of it has to do with the perfectionist side of my personality. 

For me 2023 is going to be a less is more approach. I only want to post and focus on things that I am inspired by and most proud of. Less obligation and more personal enjoyment and fulfillment. 

So here is kicking off the year with one of my absolute favorite shoots to date with @valoriedarling and @bliss.beach

There are many many more where these came from that I can’t wait to share!

Lately I have had the pleasure of photographing couples in some pretty awesome cars but this one takes the cake for me. Definitely adding this #Porsche to my dream day! 🖤🖤

What keeps you inspired? 

As a wedding photographer, I take hundreds of thousands of images a year. Yes I know that’s insane and sooo much culling. But because of that, it’s really easy to become numb to your own photography and feel “meh” about it from time to time. Especially the longer you spend on social media.

I was in a client’s home recently whom I’ve had the pleasure of photographing their life’s biggest memories for almost a decade. Their walls were filled with my images. Almost every corner of the house had a photograph that I had taken and I thought, wow, that’s pretty dang awesome. It’s easy to loose sight of your why when you spend too much time focusing on how you can improve. This was a great reminder that the work we do  lives far beyond the squares of this platform. I wanted to share this incase you needed a little friendly reminder like I did 😉

Santorini - basically heaven on earth💙🤍

Traveling has always been one of my passions, and there's nothing quite like exploring new destinations and cultures. I am so excited for all the new adventures that await this year, in particular Sicily and South France. How about you? Are you going anywhere exciting this year?

The location, the design, the attention to detail, the execution, the 100’s of amazing conversations with some of the most impressive and incredible humans in the wedding industry…just all of it.  @weddex and @kathrynarce what you have created is so beautiful and I can not thank you enough. Also major shout out to the incredible vendor team for producing such an amazing week. We were all so very spoiled by your time and talent!! Also major thanks to @allanzepedaphoto for taking the most beautiful travel pictures to document our time there because I barely took any of my own 🤦🏻‍♂️

My heart breaks for Maui. 

This beautiful island and it’s people hold a special place in my heart along with my family and close friends. Thank you to everyone who has reached out and checked in on us. We have been trying to process all that has happened and figure out the best way to serve this incredible community at such a tragic and devastating time. 

Here is the best information that we have gathered from our friends and family in maui on ways you can help right now.

- if you know someone individually affected by the fires please donate funds directly to that person through Venmo as the funds are available significantly faster than through a larger organization.  If you don’t know anyone but want to know how you can help please message me and I will send you the verified accounts of a few friends of mine who could really use it right now 

- if you have access to housing or know anyone in need of housing please get in contact with me, we have created a group of properties that are working hard to place displaced families. There are many property managers working hard at doing the same thing but the goal is to get people placed as quickly as possible and everyone is understaffed at the moment. 

- photo/ video peeps. If you have any unused gear now is the time to part with it so we can get our photo video community back to work as quickly as possible so they can start providing for their families again. I will be making a trip to Maui soon exact timing is TBD 

- other great resources are Maui Food Bank and Samaritan purse

Here is a little confession…

I’m not the best at talking about myself. You would think after all these years and hundreds if not thousands of interviews and conversations later that I would be more comfortable when the inevitable questions come up “so tell me about yourself” “or what do you feel like makes you different from your peers”?

I am confident in my answer and my abilities but I still have a hard time verbalizing them out of a fear of coming across arrogant or cocky. It’s so far off from who I am that I think I over compensate and sell myself short. So for today here is to getting more comfortable with the uncomfortable!

I make people feel comfortable, understood and beautiful…nearly instantly because I genuinely care to know them and learn about their story. I can walk into any room, with any person or personality type, no matter the situation and make them feel like they are the only one in the room within minutes. Pair that with a ridiculous attention to detail and it results in beautifully refined photos that feel genuine, authentic and emotional. When we leave a wedding weekend we are almost always told “you are part of our family now”. Not just new friends but family.  I don’t know a better compliment then that. 

So although I am literally cringing typing these words out and hesitate hitting the post button I am always looking for ways to grow in my discomforts so if you have made it this far thank you for allowing me the privilege to share a little bit more about me and partaking in my journey!

I can’t believe it.

We just finished shooting our last wedding of the season and I still can’t believe that I have been photographing weddings for MORE than half of my life.

It feels very surreal to think about and you would think I would be completely burned out by now. But the funny thing is I feel completely the opposite.  I feel more invigorated and excited about this job and this industry than I ever have.

2024 is going to be our best year yet and I can’t wait to share some of the many exciting projects underway. One of which is my official coaching platform.

So if you have an exciting year ahead and want to figure out the best way to capitalize and leverage your momentum, send me a DM so we can chat and strategize together!
